      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "When you start talking about \"ancestral lineages,\" you are moving into the realm of genetic predisposition, which is vastly more complex than simple racial categorization. While genetics absolutely dictate individual traits, trying to map those traits onto broad continental groups is scientifically reductive and often leads to biased assumptions. The performance differences you see in elite sports are almost always the result of intense, specific training environments, nutrition, and years of dedicated practice, not some fixed blueprint tied to ancestry.",
